1
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:43,100
<i>Coleen, this is Arjun,
my executive assistant.</i>

2
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:43,867
<i> Attorney.</i>

3
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,300
<i> Artemio Vital, my lawyer.</i>

4
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:49,967
<i>I coordinated with Atty. Yeban
about filing for bail.</i>

5
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:53,033
<i>We're working on the paperwork
as we speak.</i>

6
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:54,900
<i> You're getting out.</i>

7
00:00:55,033 --> 00:00:56,600
<i> Thank you, Uncle.</i>

8
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:58,133
<i>They said Coleen
has already posted bail.</i>

9
00:00:58,267 --> 00:00:59,567
<i> How did that happen?</i>

10
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:03,367
<i>Mrs. Cruz, there are exceptions.</i>

11
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,700
<i>And it still depends
on the executive judge.</i>

12
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:09,033
<i>Maybe they personally know him.</i>

13
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:09,967
<i> Who are they?</i>

14
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:12,967
<i> A certain Atty. Artemio Vital,</i>

15
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:14,933
<i>who's representing
Noah Salvador.</i>

16
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:16,233
<i> Noah,</i>

17
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:18,800
<i>thank you so much
for helping Coleen.</i>

18
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:22,167
<i>I'm just glad to be of help
to my daughter...</i>

19
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,233
<i> what I mean is the people...</i>

20
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:25,867
<i> I consider family.</i>

21
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:32,867
<i> I don't even know what to say.</i>

22
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,933
<i>I didn't expect
you'd still be here.</i>

23
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:38,367
<i>Felma, you were once a very
important part of my life.</i>

24
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,200
<i> Again, thank you.</i>

25
00:01:58,533 --> 00:02:00,667
Sir, excuse me.

26
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,900
The car is ready.

27
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:04,833
We have a flight to catch.

28
00:02:07,033 --> 00:02:07,933
Arjun,

29
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:11,100
rebook my flight going home.

30
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,833
I'll stick around for a while.

31
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:19,533
And free my schedule
for the next two weeks.

32
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:22,000
Yes, Sir.

33
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:35,900
Darn it.

34
00:02:38,967 --> 00:02:40,333
So annoying.

35
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:44,100
Coleen hasn't even warmed
her seat in jail,

36
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:46,067
and they already let her out.

37
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,533
So Noah's a big shot?

38
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:49,333
He's really influential.

39
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:51,100
Are you trying to annoy me?

40
00:02:51,233 --> 00:02:52,733
What "influential"
are you talking about?

41
00:02:52,867 --> 00:02:55,167
Coleen will still end up
behind bars.

42
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:58,967
But Coleen and Felma now have
an even bigger support system.

43
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,533
The stronger they get,

44
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:02,767
the more determined they are
to fight back.

45
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:04,500
What are you trying to say?

46
00:03:04,633 --> 00:03:05,867
They are on full force?

47
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,267
Happy family?

48
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:10,367
So Noah's just the extra wheel?

49
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,767
But you know what?
With his status...

50
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:15,600
I doubt he'd let himself
be just an extra wheel.

51
00:03:15,733 --> 00:03:17,367
He once fell head over heels
with Felma.

52
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:18,400
Who knows?

53
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:20,800
He might try
to win her over again.

54
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:22,467
And so what?

55
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,467
Felma won't entertain him.

56
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,167
Felma loves Manuel, remember?

57
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:29,033
Felma doesn't have
to be in love with Noah

58
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,733
to be in a relationship
with him.

59
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:32,467
It might actually be better
if they end up together.

60
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,667
So I can easily
take Manuel back.

61
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,100
How?

62
00:03:36,233 --> 00:03:37,967
Your husband is mad
at you, remember?

63
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:40,667
Because you keep picking
fights with him over Jessica.

64
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,500
Will you waste your time
on that?

65
00:03:42,633 --> 00:03:45,567
You're still mourning the loss
of your child.

66
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:49,500
You're even fighting for her
to get justice.

67
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:52,633
Alice, all my moves
are connected.

68
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:54,067
So better keep your eyes open.

69
00:03:54,233 --> 00:03:56,067
Just watch and learn.

70
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:06,200
There you go, sweetie. I've had
Didang replace your bedsheet.

71
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,033
So you'll have
a good night's sleep.

72
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:09,500
Thank you, bro.

73
00:04:09,633 --> 00:04:11,300
We'll have a good night's sleep,
too.

74
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:15,433
Because we know
you're just in the other room.

75
00:04:15,567 --> 00:04:16,967
Right.

76
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:20,133
And it's hard to sleep
in the cell.

77
00:04:20,267 --> 00:04:22,400
I'm really glad Uncle Noah came.

78
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:23,833
Yeah.

79
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:26,133
And...

80
00:04:26,267 --> 00:04:29,500
I'm glad he still cares for us.

81
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:31,500
It's like we have two dads.

82
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:35,933
But it would've been better
if things between them is okay.

83
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:38,833
They seemed awkward
with each other, right?

84
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:41,267
Were they awkward earlier?

85
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:44,033
Is that why you kicked me, sis?

86
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,100
They're not just the ones
who feel awkward.

87
00:04:48,233 --> 00:04:49,567
Jeff and I, too.

88
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:51,300
I don't know

89
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:54,367
how I'll act or what I'll say
when they're both there.

90
00:04:55,767 --> 00:04:58,400
I'm really thankful
to Uncle Noah.

91
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:03,100
But I don't know
how to express it...

92
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:05,667
without offending Dad.

93
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,967
And whatever we say to Dad,

94
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:11,200
we have to make sure Uncle Noah
doesn't feel out of place.

95
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:14,600
We should also consider how
that will be perceived by Mom.

96
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,567
You know what?

97
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:21,233
Don't worry about that for now.

98
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:23,600
Let's just be thankful
that I'm out of jail.

99
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:25,000
And I'm back home.

100
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:26,467
So...

101
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,767
let's sleep together tonight.

102
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,233
- Good?
- That's good.

103
00:05:31,367 --> 00:05:32,233
Here.

104
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:33,300
- I'm okay with it.
- I'm getting ready.

105
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:34,800
But are you sure
you're sleeping beside him?

106
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:36,167
He snores so loudly.

107
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:37,133
Wow.

108
00:05:37,267 --> 00:05:38,167
You're so mean.

109
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,033
But at least I only snore
when I'm sleeping.

110
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:39,967
Unlike you,
who snore when laughing.

111
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:43,333
Hey! No!

112
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:44,667
That's not true!

113
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:54,000
Felma.

114
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:58,833
Hopefully, you can finally
get some rest now that...

115
00:05:58,967 --> 00:06:01,100
Coleen's here.

116
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:02,967
You too, right?

117
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:05,867
Yes.

118
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,967
Thanks to Noah.

119
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:10,200
I didn't know
he was such a good person.

120
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:11,633
Yes, he is.

121
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:18,167
And please don't get me wrong.

122
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,967
But...

123
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,600
when you weren't here,

124
00:06:23,733 --> 00:06:25,867
Noah helped me raise the kids.

125
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:29,600
He helped me...

126
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:31,200
with work...

127
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:33,167
and with raising them.

128
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,900
Especially Coleen.

129
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:41,533
He treated the kids
like his own.

130
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,533
I was also thankful for that.

131
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:49,667
Because when I wasn't here,

132
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,433
he picked up where I fell short.

133
00:06:51,567 --> 00:06:53,933
And now he's helping Coleen.

134
00:06:54,067 --> 00:06:55,000
You know what...

135
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:57,700
I'll be forever thankful.

136
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:01,333
Yeah. I'm also grateful
to know that...

137
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,600
he has already moved on

138
00:07:04,733 --> 00:07:06,100
with what happened to us.

139
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,367
Yeah, I noticed.

140
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,900
You're still friends.

141
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,467
That's all there
is to it, Manuel.

142
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,433
Noah's helping us
with no hidden agenda.

143
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:21,733
Of course.

144
00:07:21,867 --> 00:07:23,967
We shouldn't give
it another meaning.

145
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,267
He's helping our daughter.

146
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:35,167
Wow!

147
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:38,233
He's like a knight
in shining armor, sis.

148
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:40,900
How does it feel

149
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:42,667
when your ex suddenly swoops in
to save you?

150
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,433
Oh, sorry. Second ex.

151
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:47,633
Because your first ex is Manuel.

152
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:53,900
I don't feel anything
but gratitude.

153
00:07:54,267 --> 00:07:56,467
Really? Just gratitude?

154
00:07:56,600 --> 00:08:00,533
You didn't feel your heart
skip even once?

155
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:04,133
Admit it, sis. You loved him.

156
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,233
Bro,

157
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:08,833
as far as I know,

158
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:11,500
Felma never fell in love
with Noah.

159
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:15,633
Because it's you
who Felma loves.

160
00:08:15,767 --> 00:08:18,400
So, there's nothing
to be jealous about.

161
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,667
Why? Is Manuel jealous?

162
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,767
I don't think so.

163
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,967
And I assured him that

164
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:30,533
Noah's helping us
without any hidden agenda.

165
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:33,800
Sis, don't be too sure

166
00:08:33,933 --> 00:08:37,100
that Noah's help comes
with no strings attached.

167
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,633
Girl!

168
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:40,033
Sis,

169
00:08:40,167 --> 00:08:42,100
stop it. Someone might hear you.

170
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:43,767
If you were in my shoes...

171
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,600
Imagine...

172
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:48,167
someone going after Paz,

173
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:51,533
and it happens to be her ex.

174
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:53,133
Would that be alright with you?

175
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,433
Of course not.

176
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,933
She's my wife.

177
00:08:57,233 --> 00:09:00,733
I'll beat that guy to a pulp.

178
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:03,067
That's what I'm talking about.

179
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:09,067
But Paz is your wife.
You have the right.

180
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,400
Felma and I are not
in a relationship.

181
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,433
And we can't be together

182
00:09:14,567 --> 00:09:17,167
until my marriage to Hazel
is annulled.

183
00:09:19,033 --> 00:09:22,500
I have no right to stop Noah
from getting near her.

184
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,300
Why?

185
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:28,500
Would you stop him?

186
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,967
Then you're jealous.

187
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:37,267
Manuel has nothing
to worry about.

188
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,600
He knows that he's
the one I love.

189
00:09:41,067 --> 00:09:42,933
And Noah knows it, too.

190
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:46,033
But I'm just wondering...

191
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:48,267
why he returned.

192
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,667
And why did he suddenly
help you?

193
00:09:52,233 --> 00:09:53,467
Because...

194
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,700
he loves Coleen?

195
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:57,467
And it didn't change.

196
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:01,233
And so are his feelings for you,
sis!

197
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:04,067
Noah's still in love with you.

198
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:07,133
Come on. Stop it now.

199
00:10:07,267 --> 00:10:09,733
Before anything
else happens.

200
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:11,500
You're making me nervous.

201
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:14,100
Sis. I'll bet you
my monthly salary.

202
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:15,200
Actually, scratch that.

203
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:19,233
Just half. Mayette hasn't sent
me anything yet.

204
00:10:19,367 --> 00:10:22,967
I really don't want to doubt
Noah's intentions in helping us.

205
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,200
Of course,
it makes me feel guilty.

206
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,033
He's helping, and I'm thinking
badly about him.

207
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,200
But I can't help
thinking about that.

208
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:35,333
It's because...

209
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,267
you love Felma.

210
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:41,300
It makes me
feel small, man.

211
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:44,833
When I wasn't here,

212
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:48,567
he'd been stepping in for me,

213
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:51,700
he's still doing it now.

214
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:56,333
Being here isn't enough.

215
00:10:56,467 --> 00:11:00,933
I have to be wealthy and
powerful just to help my family.

216
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:04,633
You know what, bro.

217
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:07,433
You can still help
in another way.

218
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,833
Like this.

219
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:11,567
You learned that
so you can earn some money.

220
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:13,400
I know.

221
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:15,667
But it's different
when I'm employed.

222
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:19,333
I'll find people who can
actually help my family.

223
00:11:23,133 --> 00:11:24,200
Bro...

224
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:31,433
I want to get strong
enough to walk again.

225
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:35,500
Maybe there's another way
for you to walk again.

226
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:39,067
Bro, I'll do everything
for my family.

227
00:11:41,067 --> 00:11:44,000
Especially now that
Coleen's arraignment is near.

228
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:45,967
She badly needs
my support.

229
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:53,233
As I have said,

230
00:11:53,367 --> 00:11:56,833
the arraignment is just to
confirm your identity, Coleen,

231
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,200
as the accused.

232
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:01,767
And the cases that
will be charged against you.

233
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:02,733
Okay?

234
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:04,267
Coleen, dear.

235
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,933
Dad,

236
00:12:08,067 --> 00:12:09,700
Mom...

237
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,033
I'm scared.

238
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:14,000
I don't think I can handle this.

239
00:12:17,033 --> 00:12:20,467
Dear, we'll go with you
inside to support you.

240
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:24,100
We'll face the judge
together, sweetheart.

241
00:12:25,967 --> 00:12:27,533
Dear,

242
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:29,867
you can do this.

243
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,633
Jessica's watching you.

244
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,700
Keep in mind that you're
doing this for her.

245
00:12:37,533 --> 00:12:38,867
Jessica wouldn't like it

246
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,633
if she saw you losing courage,
right?

247
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:46,033
Coleen, sweetie...

248
00:12:46,167 --> 00:12:47,933
remember that you're innocent.

249
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:51,600
Just tell them the truth.

250
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:54,400
Think about the plans
you and Jessica made.

251
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:56,867
Those plans can only happen
when you're free.

252
00:12:58,267 --> 00:12:59,667
We're here for you, Coleen.

253
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:02,500
You can do it,
my dear goddaughter.

254
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:04,667
You take after your godmother.
A fighter!

255
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:08,033
There you go again, butting in.

256
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,800
Uncle Noah?

257
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:31,333
Thank you.

258
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:32,833
Here.

259
00:13:36,133 --> 00:13:37,000
Here you go, dear.

260
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:39,567
This might help you.

261
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:41,467
Thank you, Uncle.

262
00:13:41,767 --> 00:13:42,733
Noah,

263
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:45,800
what are you doing here?

264
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,633
The same thing you're doing.

265
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:51,933
Giving my full support
to Coleen.

266
00:13:55,933 --> 00:13:57,933
Dear, are you okay now?

267
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:01,333
Thank you, Uncle Noah.

268
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,433
Thank you for coming.

269
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:12,867
Coleen,

270
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,333
you can do this.

271
00:14:15,433 --> 00:14:17,633
We are all here for you.

272
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,400
We're not going to
leave you alone, dear.

273
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:21,967
Okay?

274
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,767
- Attorney Yeban.
- Mr. Salvador,

275
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:34,733
- it's good to see you again.
- Good to see you also.

276
00:14:34,867 --> 00:14:37,400
Do everything to
win this case, okay?

277
00:14:37,533 --> 00:14:39,033
They're ready, Sir.

278
00:14:39,167 --> 00:14:40,300
Thank you.

279
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:42,033
So,

280
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,500
let's go inside.

281
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:45,667
Come on.

282
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,600
All rise.

283
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:40,167
RTC Branch 17 is now in session.

284
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:45,233
Honorable Judge
Bryan Palestino presiding.

285
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:46,967
Silence is enjoined.

286
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:54,100
Read the case.

287
00:15:54,233 --> 00:15:55,533
For arraignment.

288
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:59,467
Criminal Case 2025-828.

289
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:03,100
People of the Philippines
versus Coleen Ruiz Cruz,

290
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,667
for the crime of murder,

291
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:09,200
under Article 248
of the Revised Penal Code.

292
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:10,267
Appearances.

293
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:13,167
For the people.

294
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:14,300
Your Honor,

295
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:18,833
I respectfully appear
as the private prosecutor,

296
00:16:18,967 --> 00:16:20,567
Attorney Nico Salazar.

297
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:21,900
Good morning, Your Honor.

298
00:16:22,033 --> 00:16:25,333
Attorney Butch Yeban,
representing the accused.

299
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:27,067
Are you ready
for the arraignment?

300
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,733
Yes, Your Honor.

301
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:30,467
Where's the accused?

302
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,867
Yes, Your Honor. She's here.

303
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:37,433
It's okay.

304
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:50,367
The undersigned City Prosecutor

305
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:55,067
accuses Coleen Ruiz Cruz
of the crime of murder,

306
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:58,867
defined and penalized
under Article 428

307
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,033
of the Revised Penal Code.

308
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:02,833
Committed as follows,

309
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:06,833
that on or about
November 3rd, 2025,

310
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:09,667
in the City of Quezon,
Metro Manila, Philippines,

311
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:13,133
a place within the jurisdiction
of this honorable court,

312
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:16,300
the above-named accused
by means of treachery

313
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:18,000
with intent to kill,

314
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:21,300
did then and there willfully,
unlawfully,

315
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:24,400
and feloniously push
Jessica Cruz

316
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:26,400
towards an oncoming vehicle.

317
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:30,300
Thereby hitting the latter,
which caused her death.

318
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:31,633
Contrary to law.

319
00:17:31,767 --> 00:17:32,867
How do you plead?

320
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:40,133
Do you understand the charges
against you, Ms. Cruz?

321
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:42,933
Yes, Your Honor.

322
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,933
And what is your plea?

323
00:17:50,267 --> 00:17:52,933
Not guilty, Your Honor.

324
00:17:53,067 --> 00:17:55,367
How dare you!
You're such a liar!

325
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,300
What do you mean by not guilty?

326
00:17:56,433 --> 00:17:57,500
Mrs. Cruz!

327
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,733
You killed my daughter!
You killed her!

328
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:02,033
What were you saying?

329
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:02,933
Admit it!

330
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:04,500
Don't believe
her, Your Honor.

331
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:05,767
I didn't commit any crime.

332
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:06,867
Coleen, it's okay.

333
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,167
Order in the court! Order!
Order in the court!

334
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,100
This is not yet the trial.

335
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:14,967
This proceeding is not
the proper forum for testimony.

336
00:18:16,033 --> 00:18:20,600
I'm instructing everyone to
maintain decorum in this court.

337
00:18:22,033 --> 00:18:24,200
Please schedule
the pre-trial.

338
00:19:20,067 --> 00:19:21,867
Coleen, sweetie,

339
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,267
are you still okay?

340
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:27,833
It felt so different
inside, didn't it, Mom?

341
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:32,067
I felt like I did something
wrong even though I didn't.

342
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,067
You did well, Coleen.

343
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,467
Always remember,

344
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:39,367
don't let what people say
or think get to you. Okay?

345
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:40,767
Just stick to the truth.

346
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,967
That will strengthen you.

347
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,333
Thank you, Attorney.

348
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:46,333
Thanks for your help.

349
00:19:46,467 --> 00:19:50,100
The support of the family
is what helps Coleen.

350
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:54,067
Family and friends.

351
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:57,267
Also, your godfather
and godmother.

352
00:19:57,933 --> 00:19:59,567
Sweetheart,

353
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:01,400
we're in this fight together.

354
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:03,567
Sweetie, I promise.

355
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:05,800
No matter when the hearing
is, we'll be here.

356
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:08,333
We're always present.

357
00:20:08,467 --> 00:20:10,200
We're all here for you.

358
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:12,867
Thank you, Dad.

359
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,033
Thank you, everyone.

360
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:22,667
Wait.

361
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:25,833
Where's Noah?

362
00:20:34,067 --> 00:20:36,233
We're sorry.
The number you have reached...

363
00:20:46,367 --> 00:20:47,900
Who are you calling?

364
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:50,900
We're sorry.
The number you have reached...

365
00:20:51,033 --> 00:20:52,333
Noah.

366
00:20:54,167 --> 00:20:56,433
We weren't able to talk
to him earlier.

367
00:20:56,567 --> 00:21:00,367
He might think that we
didn't appreciate his presence.

368
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:03,533
I don't think so.

369
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:06,267
We were able to talk
before the arraignment.

370
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,900
Maybe he had something
important to do,

371
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:13,067
so he had to leave
without saying goodbye.

372
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,300
I guess there's no need
to call him now.

373
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:18,367
Are you jealous?

374
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:22,433
Goodness, Felma.

375
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,233
Why would I get jealous?

376
00:21:24,967 --> 00:21:27,133
Right.

377
00:21:27,267 --> 00:21:29,300
You have nothing
to be jealous about.

378
00:21:29,433 --> 00:21:31,267
Exactly.

379
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,900
You know my feelings
for you, right?

380
00:21:34,033 --> 00:21:36,067
Also,

381
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,900
our situation.

382
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:40,633
Yes.

383
00:21:42,067 --> 00:21:43,733
Nothing has changed.

384
00:21:45,067 --> 00:21:47,667
I'll still file for annulment
of my marriage with Hazel.

385
00:21:48,633 --> 00:21:50,367
So we can get married.

386
00:21:52,133 --> 00:21:53,533
I don't know. Maybe...

387
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:58,300
I'm not used to him being here.

388
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:02,700
I'm used to us being the only
ones who care about our kids.

389
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,933
Forget it. Don't worry about it.

390
00:22:05,067 --> 00:22:06,800
What matters is that
he helped Coleen.

391
00:22:06,933 --> 00:22:08,700
By any means.

392
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,533
Thank you for
understanding, Manuel.

393
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:21,867
I only want...

394
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,333
to assure you that...

395
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:27,133
Noah and I are just friends.

396
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:29,033
That's it.

397
00:22:49,633 --> 00:22:51,367
Hi.

398
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:53,667
Thank you for accepting
my invitation.

399
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:57,033
You want anything? Coffee?

400
00:23:01,033 --> 00:23:02,367
I don't have all day.

401
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:06,367
Tell me what I need to know.

402
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:10,200
Direct to the point.

403
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,367
I like that.

404
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:13,900
Exactly what I want.

405
00:23:14,033 --> 00:23:15,733
Fine.

406
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:17,967
I'll get straight to the point.

407
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:23,033
I want us to be allies.

408
00:23:26,767 --> 00:23:27,700
What?

409
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:30,567
We both want the same thing.

410
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:33,800
Be with the ones we love.

411
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:37,833
You know what...

412
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,333
I think I already
heard this.

413
00:23:41,233 --> 00:23:43,867
I don't give up easily, Noah.

414
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:47,500
I feel that you still love Felma
so much.

415
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:50,067
I feel the same way
about Manuel.

416
00:23:51,967 --> 00:23:54,700
So let's work together

417
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,467
so you can get Felma,

418
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:59,000
and I can take my husband back.

419
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:11,967
I saw two women fighting
on the sidewalk.

420
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:14,233
One of them is Coleen Cruz.

421
00:24:14,367 --> 00:24:16,467
She pushed the victim.

422
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,033
It happened so fast.

423
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:21,767
I tried to brake, but I ended up
hitting the woman.

424
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:23,567
That's not true!

425
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:26,833
He's lying!
I didn't push my sister!

426
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:28,667
No matter what I do,

427
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,800
I still can't encourage Coleen.

428
00:24:30,933 --> 00:24:32,600
It seems not enough.

429
00:24:32,733 --> 00:24:35,100
You don't have
to do it all.

430
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:37,367
Andrea and Jeffrey are there,

431
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:38,800
Manuel is too,

432
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:41,400
and I'm here.

433
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:47,500
I'm not doing this
to ruin their family.

434
00:24:47,633 --> 00:24:50,200
You're not back in Felma's life
for Coleen's sake.

435
00:24:50,333 --> 00:24:53,467
The truth is,
you saw your chance.

436
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:58,433
You helped Coleen just to
be the hero in Felma's eyes.
